OL,3,CJersey looks to Guernsey for recycling
OL,4,Cinspiration
OL,6,FThe system sees households paying for
OL,7,Fstickers on every black bin bag left
OL,8,Fout for collection; meanwhile,
OL,9,Fcollection of recycling and food waste
OL,10,Ffrom the kerbside is free across the
OL,11,Fisland.
OL,13,FStickers cost #1.88 for a 50-litre
OL,14,Fgeneral waste bag, or #3.38 for a 90-
OL,15,Flitre bag.
OL,17,FGuernsey also recycles a wider range
OL,18,Fof waste items - such as milk and
OL,19,Fjuice cartons, or plastic food
OL,20,Fcontainers.
