OL,3,CJersey looks to Guernsey for recycling
OL,4,Cinspiration
OL,6,FJennifer adds that Guernsey appears to
OL,7,Fachieved a cultural shift when it
OL,8,Fcomes to attitudes regarding waste
OL,9,Fdisposal.
OL,11,F"We have about 348 kilograms of waste
OL,12,F(per person) and they have about 118.
OL,14,F"So when they made the change to the
OL,15,Fnew system they are now producing a
OL,16,Flot less waste overall - which
OL,17,Fsuggests that people are actively
OL,18,Fchoosing to reject, to repair, or to
OL,19,Freuse."
